article.description: — Tylor Perry tied his season high with 23 points as North Texas beat Wichita State 62-52 on Saturday.
article.headline: Perry scores 23, lifts North Texas over Wichita State 62-52
article.linkText: Perry scores 23, lifts North Texas over Wichita State 62-52
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- — Tylor Perry tied his season high with 23 points as North Texas beat Wichita State 62-52 on Saturday. Perry converted all 10 of his foul shots. Thomas Bell had 13 points for the Mean Green (7-3), who notched their fifth straight victory. Abou Ousmane added 10 points. Morris Udeze had 17 points for the Shockers (8-3). Craig Porter Jr. added 12 points. Wichita State totaled a season-low 18 second-half points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
